---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="DIDCore — DID One" description="The identity kernel for DID One Identity Platform.">
  <main class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="badge">DIDCore</div>
      <h1>DIDCore</h1>
      <p class="lede">DIDCore is the identity kernel: the place where identity becomes stable enough for agents, commerce, governance, and worlds to exist.</p>
      <div class="panel">
        <pre class="code-card">DIDCore =
  DID
  + DID Document
  + Controller
  + Verification Method
  + Wallet Binding
  + Credential Anchor
  + Lifecycle State
  + Recovery Policy
  + Compatibility Profile
  + Immutable Audit</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <div class="card"><h3>DID</h3><p>The canonical identifier for humans, agents, tools, skills, credentials, APIs, devices, organizations, and worlds.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Controller</h3><p>The authority that can control, recover, rotate, constrain, or retire the identity.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Verification</h3><p>Verification methods, proofs, service endpoints, credential anchors, and status checks.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
